reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 21, 2023
reviews.reviewText: The write speed it not very fast but for the price these are a good deal. They are made well and packed nicely in a box that with a foam insert that keeps the separated from each other. I will likely buy again if the price stays the same.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 2, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I ordered the ten pack of 32gig Flash Drives. So far, I've tried to load photos on 5 of them. All 5 have "corrupted" before I could finalize the transfer and gives me Drive D error messages when i try to use them. I tried to use them on 3 different computers and all 3 give me the same error messages.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 14, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Couple of drives failed to open
reviews.reviewText: I have bought these several times and never had any problems and they have always worked like a charm. But on this most recent purchase. I bought a quantity 20 ( 2 boxes of 10) Out of the 2 boxes , a total of 2 drives failed to open. Not that this will discourage me from purchasing again. But on my next purchase, I will be testing all drives upon receipt.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars These things hold a LOT of music!
reviews.reviewText: I bought these to keep one in my car's data port so I could listen to my music. I like how tiny they are. The only problem I had was more my car's issue--it needed the drive to be formatted as Fat32 and these come in another format. Windows couldn't do it, but a simple, free downloaded app did the formatting nicely. Then, just drag and drop to copy files. It works great and I have four spares.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Waste of money. Dont Work. Data just disappears. CANNOT be trusted with any data.
reviews.reviewText: These drives are a huge waste of time and money. Do not buy these drives is you value your data. Even for a quick move from one machine to another - you'll be missing files that it said were copied, the drives, even after safely removing them from the machine via Windows Remove and Eject. Every single time I plug these into my computer the disk is corrupted and needs to be fixed through chkdsk.Please buy something else - anything else. These should be removed from Amazon completely due to their lack of function, and safety of your data.
